name: Lord Snow
cap: But it's not all of 'em's done bad things.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Some of 'em's just poor lads looking for steady feed.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Some of 'em's high-born lads looking for glory.

name: Lord Snow
cap: They have a better chance finding feed than glory.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The Night's Watch is a joke to you, is it?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Is that what we are, Lannister? An army of jesters in black?

name: Lord Snow
cap: You don't have enough men to be an army

name: Lord Snow
cap: and, aside from Yoren here, none of you are particularly funny.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I hope we've provided you with some good stories to tell

name: Lord Snow
cap: when you're back in King's Landing.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's something to think about while you're drinking your wine down there,

name: Lord Snow
cap: enjoying your brothels.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Half the boys you've seen training will die north of the Wall.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Might be a wildling's axe that gets them,

name: Lord Snow
cap: might be sickness,

name: Lord Snow
cap: might just be the cold.

name: Lord Snow
cap: They die in pain.

name: Lord Snow
cap: And they do it...

name: Lord Snow
cap: so plump little lords like you can enjoy their summer afternoons in peace and comfort.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Do you think I'm plump?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Listen, Benjen... May I call you Benjen? - Call me what you like.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I'm not sure what I've done to offend you.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I have great admiration for the Night's Watch.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I've great admiration for you as First Ranger.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You know, my brother once told me...

name: Lord Snow
cap: that nothing someone says before the word 'but' really counts.

name: Lord Snow
cap: But...

name: Lord Snow
cap: I don't believe that giants and ghouls and white walkers

name: Lord Snow
cap: are lurking beyond the Wall.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I believe that the only difference between us and the wildlings

name: Lord Snow
cap: is that when that wall went up, our ancestors happened

name: Lord Snow
cap: to live on the right side of it.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You're right.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The wildlings are no different from us.

name: Lord Snow
cap: A little rougher maybe.

name: Lord Snow
cap: But they're made of meat and bone.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I know how to track them and I know how to kill them.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's not the wildlings giving me sleepless nights.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You've never been north of the Wall, so don't tell me what's out there.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Are you going below?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Keep well, keep warm. - Enjoy the capital, brother.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Oh, I always do.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I think he's starting to like me.

name: Lord Snow
cap: 'Going below'? - Aye.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Into the tunnel and out the other side.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He'll be north of the Wall for a month or two.

name: Lord Snow
cap: So... you're heading down to King's Landing too.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Aye, day after tomorrow.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I get about half of my recruits from their dungeons.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Let's share the road. I could use some decent company.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I, er...

name: Lord Snow
cap: I travel a bit on the grubby side, my lord.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Not this time. We'll be staying at the finest castles and inns.

name: Lord Snow
cap: No one turns away a Lannister.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Yes, Khaleesi.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Oh, what are you doing?

name: Lord Snow
cap: When was last time you bleed, Khaleesi?

name: Lord Snow
cap: You change, Khaleesi.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's a blessing from the Great Stallion

name: Lord Snow
cap: For a man on horseback, the curved blade is a good thing,

name: Lord Snow
cap: easier to handle.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's a good weapon for a Dothrakan.

name: Lord Snow
cap: But a man in full plate...

name: Lord Snow
cap: ...the arakh won't get through the steel.

name: Lord Snow
cap: That's where the broadsword has the advantage.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Designed for piercing plate.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Dothraki don't wear steel dresses.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Armour. - Armour.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Armour make a man, erm...

name: Lord Snow
cap: Slow.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Slow. - It's true, but it also keeps a man alive.

name: Lord Snow
cap: My father taught me how to fight.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He taught me that speed defeats size.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I've heard that your father was a famous warrior.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He was bloodrider to Khal Bharbo.

name: Lord Snow
cap: And your father, Jorah the Andal? He was a warrior also?

name: Lord Snow
cap: He still is.

name: Lord Snow
cap: A man of great honour

name: Lord Snow
cap: and I betrayed him.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The Khaleesi wants to eat something different tonight.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Kill some rabbits.

name: Lord Snow
cap: There are no rabbits.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Find some ducks, she likes ducks.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Have you seen any ducks, woman? No rabbits, no ducks.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Do you have eyes in your head? Do you?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Dog then. I have seen many dogs.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I don't think she wants to eat dog.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The khaleesi have baby inside her.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It is true. She does not bleed for two moons.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Her belly start to swell.

name: Lord Snow
cap: A blessing from the Great Stallion.

name: Lord Snow
cap: She does not want to eat horse.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I'll have the boys butcher a goat for supper.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I need to ride to Qohor.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Uh, we ride for Vaes Dothrak.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Don't worry. I'll catch you.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The horde's easy to find.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Don't stand so still. It's harder to hit a moving target.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Except for you. You move too much.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I could just hold my sword out and let you do the work for me.

name: Lord Snow
cap: How many winters have you seen, Lord Tyrion?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Eight. No, nine.

name: Lord Snow
cap: All of them brief?

name: Lord Snow
cap: They say the winter of my birth was three years long, Maester Aemon.

name: Lord Snow
cap: This summer has lasted nine.

name: Lord Snow
cap: But reports from the citadel tell us the days grow shorter.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The Starks are always right eventually -

name: Lord Snow
cap: winter is coming.

name: Lord Snow
cap: This one will be long...

name: Lord Snow
cap: and dark things will come with it.

name: Lord Snow
cap: We've been capturing wildlings, more every month.

name: Lord Snow
cap: They're fleeing south.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The ones who flee... say they've seen the white walkers.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Yes, and the fishermen of Lannisport say they see mermaids.

name: Lord Snow
cap: One of our own rangers swore he saw them kill his companions.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He swore it right up to the moment Ned Stark chopped his head off.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The Night's Watch is the only thing standing between the realm

name: Lord Snow
cap: and what lies beyond.

name: Lord Snow
cap: And it has become an army of undisciplined boys and tired old men.

name: Lord Snow
cap: There are less than a thousand of us now.

name: Lord Snow
cap: We can't man the other castles on the Wall.

name: Lord Snow
cap: We can't properly patrol the wilderness.

name: Lord Snow
cap: We've barely enough resources to keep our lads armed and fed.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Your sister sits by the side of the king.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Tell her... we need help.

name: Lord Snow
cap: When winter does come, gods help us all if we're not ready.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's a boy.

name: Lord Snow
cap: How do you know?

name: Lord Snow
cap: I know.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I'm sorry to see you leave, Lannister.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's either me or this cold,

name: Lord Snow
cap: and it doesn't appear to be going anywhere.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Will you stop at Winterfell on your way south?

name: Lord Snow
cap: I expect I will.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Gods know there aren't many feather beds between here and King's Landing.

name: Lord Snow
cap: If you see my brother Bran,

name: Lord Snow
cap: tell him I miss him.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Tell him I'd visit if I could.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Of course.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He'll never walk again.

name: Lord Snow
cap: If you're going to be a cripple, it's better to be a rich cripple.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You take care, Snow.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Farewell, my lord.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You are late, boy.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Tomorrow you will be here at midday.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Who are you?

name: Lord Snow
cap: Your dancing master, Syrio Forel.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Tomorrow you will catch it.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Now pick it up.

name: Lord Snow
cap: That is not the way, boy.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It is not a greatsword that is needing two hands to swing it.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It's too heavy. - It is heavy as it needs to be

name: Lord Snow
cap: to make you strong.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Just so.

name: Lord Snow
cap: One hand is all that is needed.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Now you are standing all wrong.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Turn your body sideface.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Yes.

name: Lord Snow
cap: So.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You are skinny. That is good.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The target is smaller.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Now the grip - let me see.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Yes.

name: Lord Snow
cap: The grip must be delicate.

name: Lord Snow
cap: What if I drop it?

name: Lord Snow
cap: The steel must be part of your arm.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Can you drop part of your arm? No.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Nine years Syrio Forel was first sword to the Sealord of Braavos.

name: Lord Snow
cap: He knows these things. You must listen to me, boy.

name: Lord Snow
cap: I'm a girl.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Boy, girl... You are a sword, that is all.

name: Lord Snow
cap: That is the grip.

name: Lord Snow
cap: You are not holding a battle-axe. You are holding...

name: Lord Snow
cap: A needle.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ahhh.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Just so.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Now we will begin the dance.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Remember, child,

name: Lord Snow
cap: this is not the dance of the Westeros we are learning...

name: Lord Snow
cap: The knight's dance, hacking and hammering.

name: Lord Snow
cap: This is the Braavos dance...

name: Lord Snow
cap: the water dance.

name: Lord Snow
cap: It is swift...

name: Lord Snow
cap: and sudden.

name: Lord Snow
cap: All men are made of water.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Do you know this?

name: Lord Snow
cap: If you pierce them,

name: Lord Snow
cap: the water leaks out and they die.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Now you will try to strike me.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ha!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Up!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ha!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ah.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Dead.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Oh!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Dead.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Hup!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Very dead.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Come.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ah ah ah!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Hup!

name: Lord Snow
cap: Again, faster.

name: Lord Snow
cap: Ah.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The little lord's been dreaming again.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We have visitors. - I don't want to see anyone.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Really? If I was cooped up all day

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: with no one but this old bat for company, I'd go mad.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Anyway, you don't have a choice. Robb's waiting.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I don't want to go. - Neither do I.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But Robb's Lord of Winterfell,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: which means I do what he says, and you do what I say.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hodor!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hodor? - Help Bran down the hall.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hodor.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I must say I received a slightly warmer welcome on my last visit.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Any man of the Night's Watch is welcome at Winterfell.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Any man of the Night's Watch, but not I, eh, boy?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm not your boy, Lannister.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm Lord of Winterfell while my father is away.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Then you might learn a lord's courtesy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So it's true.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hello, Bran.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you remember anything about what happened?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He has no memory of that day.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Curious. - Why are you here?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Would your charming companion be so kind as to kneel?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My neck is beginning to hurt. - Kneel, Hodor.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you like to ride, Bran? - Yes.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Well, I mean I did like to.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The boy has lost the use of his legs. - What of it?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: With the right horse and saddle, even a cripple can ride.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm not a cripple. - Then I'm not a dwarf.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My father will rejoice to hear it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I have a gift for you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Give that to your saddler. He'll provide the rest.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You must shape the horse to the rider.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Start with a yearling and teach it to respond to the reins and to the boy's voice.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Will I really be able to ride? - You will.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: On horseback you will be as tall as any of them.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Is this some kind of trick? Why do you want to help him?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I have a tender spot in my heart for cripples, bastards and broken things.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You've done my brother a kindness.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The hospitality of Winterfell is yours.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Spare me your false courtesies, Lord Stark. There's a brothel outside your walls.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: There I'll find a bed and both of us can sleep easier.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Couldn't resist some northern arse?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If you like Redheads, ask for Ros.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Come to see me off, Greyjoy? Kind of you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your master doesn't seem to like Lannisters.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He's not my master. - No, of course not.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What happened here? Where is Lady Stark? Why didn't she receive me?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She wasn't feeling well. - She's not in Winterfell, is she?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Where did she go? - M'lady's whereabouts...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: M'lady?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your loyalty to your captors is touching.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Tell me, how do you think Balon Greyjoy would feel

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: if he could see his only surviving son has turned lackey?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I still remember seeing my father's fleet burn in Lannisport.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I believe your uncles were responsible. - Must have been a pretty sight.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Nothing prettier than watching sailors burn alive.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yes, a great victory for your people. Shame how it all turned out.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We were outnumbered ten to one. - A stupid rebellion, then.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I suppose your father realised that when your brothers died in battle.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Now here you are, your enemy's squire.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Careful, Imp. - I've offended you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Forgive me, it's been a rough morning.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Anyway, don't despair.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm a constant disappointment to my own father

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and I've learned to live with it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your next tumble with Ros is on me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'll try not to wear her out.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Shoulder, legs.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Leg, shoulder, leg.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Left foot forward. Good.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Now pivot as you deliver the stroke. Put all your weight behind it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What in seven hells is that?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They'll need an eighth hell to fit him in.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Tell them your name.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Samwell Tarly,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: of Horn Hill... I mean, I was of Horn Hill.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I've come to take the black.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Come to take the black pudding.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Well, you couldn't be any worse than you look.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Rast...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: see what he can do.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I yield.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Please, no more. - On your feet.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Pick up your sword.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hit him till he finds his feet.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It seems they've run short of poachers and thieves down south.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Now they send us squealing bloody pigs. - Jon!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Again, harder.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I yield! - Enough!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He yielded.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Looks like the bastard's in love.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: All right then, Lord Snow,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: you wish to defend your lady love, let's make it an exercise.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You two. Three of you ought to be sufficient

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: to make lady piggy squeal.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: All you've got to do is get past the bastard.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Are you sure you want to do this? - No.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yield, yield, yield! I yield.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We're done for today. Go clean the armoury.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: That's all you're good for.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Well fought! - Piss off.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Did he hurt you? - I've had worse.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You can call me Sam... if you want.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My mother calls me Sam. - It's not going to get any easier, you know?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're going to have to defend yourself. - Why didn't you get up and fight?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I wanted to.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I just couldn't. - Why not?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm a coward.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My father always says so. - The Wall's no place for cowards.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're right. I'm sorry.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I just... wanted to thank you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A bloody coward.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: People saw us talking to him. Now they'll think we're cowards too.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're too stupid to be a coward.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're too stupid to be a... - Quick now,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: before summer's over.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Come here!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hyah, hyah!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Vaes Dothrak - the city of the horselords.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A pile of mud. Mud and shit and twigs.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Best these savages can do. - These are my people now.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You shouldn't call them savages. - I'll call them what I like,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: because they're my people. This is my army.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Khal Drogo is marching the wrong way with my army.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If my brother was given an army of Dothraki,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: could you conquer the Seven Kingdoms?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The Dothraki have never crossed the narrow sea.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They fear any water their horses can't drink.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But if they did?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: King Robert is fool enough to meet them in open battle,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: but the men advising him are different.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And you know these men? - I fought beside them once,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: long ago.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Now Ned Stark wants my head.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He drove me from my land.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You sold slaves.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Aye.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Why? - I had no money

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and an expensive wife.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And where is she now?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: In another place,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: with another man.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your Grace? - Yes, my dear?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They call you the last dragon...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They do.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You have dragon's blood in your veins?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It's entirely possible.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What happened to the dragons?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I was told that brave men killed them all.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ow.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yes. Seeing a dragon would make me very happy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Well, after 15 years in a pleasure house,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I imagine just seeing the sky makes you happy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: a man from Asshai with a dagger of real dragonglass.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ooh. - I've seen a man who could

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And I've seen a pirate who wore his weight in gold

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: have you seen one?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A pirate ship? - A dragon.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: No.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: I'll tell you what I have seen -

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They used to decorate the throne room in the Red Keep.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: Why were they killed?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: It's the Hand's Tournament that's causing all this trouble, my lords.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: I should warn you,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: 'then we'll have a hunt

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: 'Nothing would please me more.'

cap: Ser Alliser's going to make me fight again tomorrow, isn't he?

cap: I'm not going to get any better, you know.

cap: Well...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: Hmph.

cap: Do you know Ser Hugh of the Vale?

cap: Not surprising.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

cap: Get a message to this paragon of yours - discreetly.

cap: Lord Baelish, perhaps I was wrong to distrust you.

cap: Ser Hugh! - As you can see, I'm busy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gendry!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Strong for his age. He works hard.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: This is fine work. - It's not for sale.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
