name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Forgive him, my lord. - There's nothing to forgive.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: When Lord Arryn came to visit you, what would you talk about?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He just asked me questions is all, my lord.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What kind of questions?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: About my work at first,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: if I was being treated well, if I liked it here.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But then he started asking me about my mother.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your mother? - Who she was, what she looked like.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What did you tell him?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She died when I was little.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She had yellow hair.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She'd sing to me sometimes.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Look at me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Get back to work, lad.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If the day ever comes when that boy would rather wield a sword than forge one,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: you send him to me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Find anything?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: King Robert's bastard son.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He likes that.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: This is for the king from Lord Stark.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Should I leave it with...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Shhh. Listen.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you hear them?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: How many do you think are in there with him? Huh?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Guess. - Three.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Four.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He likes to do this when I'm on duty.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He makes me listen as he insults my sister.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Forgive me, my lord... - Why do I have to forgive you?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Have you wronged me?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We've met before, you know. - Have we? Strange, I've forgotten.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The siege of Pyke. We fought side by side one afternoon.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ah.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: That's where you got your scar? - Aye.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Oh. - One of the Greyjoys nearly took my eye.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Vicious sons of whores. - They like their bloodshed.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They stopped liking it at the end.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: That was a proper battle.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you remember Thoros of Myr charging through the breach?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: With his burning sword? I'll remember that till the day I die.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I saw the youngest of the Greyjoy lads at Winterfell.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It was like seeing a shark on a mountaintop.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Theon? He's a good lad. - I doubt it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'll bet you smell of blackberry jam!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Let me smell it. Come here.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Can I leave this with you? The message from Lord Stark.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I don't serve Lord Stark.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Where have you been? - Watch duty.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: With Sam. - Ah, Prince Porkchop.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Where is he? - He wasn't hungry.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Impossible!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: That's enough.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Sam's no different from the rest of us.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: There was no place for him in the world, so he's come here.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We're not going to hurt him in the training yard anymore.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Never again, no matter what Thorne says.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He's our brother now and we're going to protect him.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You are in love, Lord Snow.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You girls can do as you please.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But if Thorne puts me up against Lady Piggy,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm gonna slice me off a side of bacon.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: No one touches Sam.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What are you waiting for?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Attack him!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You get in there.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hit me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Go on, hit me!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I yield!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yield. Yield.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I yield.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You think this is funny, do you?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: When you're out there beyond the Wall with the sun going down,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: do you want a man at your back?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Or a snivelling boy?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You send this whore to give me commands?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I should have sent you back her head!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Forgive me, Khaleesi. I did as you asked.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Hush now. It's all right. Irri, take her and leave us.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yes, Khaleesi.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Why did you hit her?! - How many times do I have to tell you?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You do not command me. - I wasn't commanding you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I just wanted to invite you to supper.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What's this? - It's a gift.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I had it made for you. - Dothraki rags?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Are you going to dress me now? - Please.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: This stinks of manure. All of it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Stop. Stop. Stop it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You would turn me into one of them, wouldn't you?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Next you'll want to braid my hair. - You've no right to a braid.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You've won no victories yet. - You do not talk back to me!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You are a horselord's slut. And now you've woken the dragon...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I am a khaleesi of the Dothraki!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I am the wife of the great khal and I carry his son inside me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The next time you raise a hand to me

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: will be the last time you have hands.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I know for a fact that some of the officers go to that brothel in Mole's Town.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I wouldn't doubt it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Don't you think it's a little bit unfair?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Making us take our vows while they sneak off for a little Sally on the side?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Sally on the side? - It's silly, isn't it?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What, we can't defend the Wall unless we're celibate?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It's absurd. - I didn't think you'd be so upset about it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Why not?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Because I'm fat?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: No. - But I like girls just as much as you do.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They might not like me as much.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I've never... been with one.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You've probably had hundreds.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: No.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: As a matter of fact,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm the same as you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yeah. Yeah, I...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I find that hard to believe.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I came very close once.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I was alone in a room with a naked girl, but...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Didn't know where to put it? - I know where to put it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Was she...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: old and ugly?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Young and gorgeous.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A whore named Ros.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What colour hair?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Red. - Oh, I like red hair.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And her, um...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Her...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You don't want to know. - What, that good?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Better. - Oh, no.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So why exactly did you not make love to Ros with the perfect?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What's my name? - Jon Snow.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And why is my surname Snow?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Because...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: you're a bastard from the North.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I never met my mother.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My father wouldn't even tell me her name.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I don't know if she's living or dead.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I don't know if she's a noblewoman or a fisherman's wife...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: or a whore.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So I sat there

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: in the brothel as Ros took off her clothes.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But I couldn't do it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Because all I could think was what if I got her pregnant

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and she had a child, another bastard named Snow?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It's not a good life for a child.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ah, mmm.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: you didn't know where to put it?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Enjoying yourselves?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You look cold, boys.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It is a bit nippy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A bit nippy, yeah, by the fire,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: indoors.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It's still summer.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you boys even remember the last winter?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: How long has it been now? What, 10 years?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I remember.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Was it uncomfortable at Winterfell?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Were there days when you just couldn't get warm,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: never mind how many fires your servants built?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I build my own fires. - That's admirable.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I spent six months out there, beyond the Wall

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: during the last winter.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It was supposed to be a two-week mission.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We heard a rumour Mance Rayder was planning to attack Eastwatch.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So we went out to look for some of his men -

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: capture them, gather some knowledge.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The wildlings who fight for Mance Rayder are hard men.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Harder than you'll ever be.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They know their country better than we do.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They knew there was a storm coming in.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: So they hid in their caves and waited for it to pass.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And we got caught in the open.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Wind so strong

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: it yanked 100-foot trees straight from the ground, roots and all.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If you took your gloves off to find your cock to have a piss,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: you lost a finger to the frost.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And all in darkness.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You don't know cold.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Neither of you do.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The horses died first.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We didn't have enough to feed them, to keep them warm.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Eating the horses was easy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But later when we started to fall...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: That wasn't easy.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We should have had a couple of boys like you along, shouldn't we?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Soft, fat boys like you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: We'd have lasted a fortnight on you and still had bones left over for soup.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Soon we'll have new recruits

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and you lot will be passed along to the lord commander

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: for assignment,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and they will call you men of the Night's Watch,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: but you'd be fools to believe it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're boys still.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And come the winter you will die...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: like flies.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I hit him.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I hit the dragon.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your brother Rhaegar was the last dragon.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Viserys is less than the shadow of a snake.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He is still the true king. - The truth now.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Do you want to see your brother sitting on the Iron Throne?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: No.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: But the common people are waiting for him.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Illyrio said they are sewing dragon banners and praying for his return.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The common people pray for rain, health and a summer that never ends.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They don't care what games the high lords play.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What do you pray for, Ser Jorah?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Home.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I pray for home too.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My brother will never take back the Seven Kingdoms.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He couldn't lead an army even if my husband gave him one.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He'll never take us home.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Lovers' quarrel?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm sorry. Do I?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Sansa dear, this is Lord Baelish.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He's known... - An old friend of the family.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I've known your mother a long, long time.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Why do they call you Littlefinger? - Arya!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Don't be rude! - No, it's quite all right.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: When I was a child, I was very small,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and I come from a little spit of land called the Fingers,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: so you see, it's an exceedingly clever nickname.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I've been sitting here for days!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Start the damn joust before I piss myself!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gods, who's that?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ser Gregor Clegane.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: They call him the Mountain.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The Hound's older brother.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And his opponent? - Ser Hugh of the Vale.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He was Jon Arryn's squire.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Look how far he's come.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Yes, yes, enough of the bloody pomp. Have at him!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Not what you were expecting?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Has anyone ever told you the story of the Mountain and the Hound?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Lovely little tale of brotherly love.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The Hound was just a pup,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: six years old maybe.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gregor a few years older,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: already a big lad, already getting a bit of a reputation.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Some lucky boys just born with a talent for violence.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: One evening Gregor found his little brother playing with a toy by the fire -

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gregor's toy,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: a wooden knight.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gregor never said a word,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: he just grabbed his brother by the scruff of his neck

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and shoved his face into the burning coals.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Held him there while the boy screamed,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: while his face melted.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: There aren't very many people who know that story.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I won't tell anyone. I promise. - No, please don't.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If the Hound so much as heard you mention it,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm afraid all the knights in King's Landing would not be able to save you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My lord, Her Grace the queen.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your Grace. - You're missing your tournament.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Putting my name on it doesn't make it mine.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I thought we might put what happened on the Kingsroad behind us -

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: the ugliness with the wolves.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And forcing you to kill the beast was extreme.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Though sometimes we go to extremes where our children are concerned.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: How is Sansa?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She likes it here. - She's the only Stark who does.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Favours her mother, not much of the North in her.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What are you doing here? - I might ask the same of you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: What is it you hope to accomplish?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The king called on me to serve him and the realm,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and that's what I'll do until he tells me otherwise.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You can't change him. You can't help him.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He'll do what he wants, which is all he's ever done.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You'll try your best to pick up the pieces.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: If that's my job, then so be it.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You're just a soldier, aren't you?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You take your orders and you carry on.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I suppose it makes sense.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Your older brother was trained to lead and you were trained to follow.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I was also trained to kill my enemies, Your Grace.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: As was I.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Seven blessings to you, goodfolk!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And to you.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Boy! Bread, meat and beer. Quickly.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Ah, good idea, Grandfather. I'm starving.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A song while we wait or? - I'd rather throw myself down a well.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Now, now, Grandfather, this may be your last chance if you're heading North.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The only music the northerners know is the howling of wolves!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Gods.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I'm sorry, my lord. We're full up.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Every room. - My men can sleep in the stable.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: As for myself, I don't require a large room.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Truly, my lord, we have nothing. - Is there nothing I can do...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: ...to remedy this?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You can have my room. - Now there's a clever man.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You can manage food, I trust? Yoren, dine with me.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Aye, my lord. - My lord of Lannister!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Might I entertain you while you eat?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I can sing of your father's victory at King's Landing!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Nothing would more likely ruin my supper.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Lady Stark! What an unexpected pleasure.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I was sorry to have missed you at Winterfell.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Lady Stark!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I was still Catelyn Tully the last time I stayed here.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: You, ser.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Is that the black bat of Harrenhal I see embroidered on your coat?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: It is, my lady.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: And is Lady Whent a true and honest friend

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: to my father, Lord Hoster Tully of Riverrun?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: She is.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: The red stallion was always a welcome sight at Riverrun.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: My father counts Jonos Bracken amongst his oldest and most loyal bannermen.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Our lord is honoured by his trust.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I envy your father all his fine friends, Lady Stark,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: but I don't quite see the purpose of this.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I know your sigil as well -

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: the twin towers of Frey.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: How fares your lord, ser?

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: Lord Walder is well, my lady.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He has asked your father for the honour of his presence on his 90th nameday.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: He plans to take another wife. - Ha!

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: This man...

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: came into my house as a guest

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and there conspired to murder my son.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: A boy of 10.

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: In the name of King Robert and the good lords you serve,

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: I call upon you to seize him

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: and help me return him to Winterfell

name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
cap: to await the king's justice.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Does Ser Hugh have any family in the capital?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I stood vigil for him myself last night.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He had no one else.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He'd never worn this armour before.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Bad luck for him - going against the Mountain.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Who determines the draw?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: All the knights draw straws, Lord Stark.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Aye.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But who holds the straws?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You've done good work, Sisters.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Life is strange.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Not so many years ago we fought as enemies at the Trident.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm glad we never met on the field, Ser Barristan.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: As is my wife. I don't think the widow's life would suit her.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're too modest.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've seen you cut down a dozen great knights.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My father once told me you were the best he'd ever seen.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I never knew the man to be wrong about matters of combat.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He was a fine man, your father.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What the Mad King did to him was a terrible crime.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And that lad -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: he was a squire until a few months ago.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How could he afford a new suit of armour?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Perhaps Lord Arryn left him some money?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I hear the king wants to joust today. - Yes, that will never happen.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Robert tends to do what he wants.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If the king got what he wanted all the time,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: he'd still be fighting a damned rebellion.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It's made too small, Your Grace. It won't go.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your mother was a dumb whore with a fat arse.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Did you know that?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Look at this idiot! One ball and no brains.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He can't even put a man's armour on him properly.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're too fat for your armour. - Fat?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Fat, is it?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is that how you speak to your king?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, it's funny, is it?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No, Your Grace. - No?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You don't like the Hand's joke?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're torturing the poor boy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You heard the Hand. The king's too fat for his armour.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Go find the breastplate stretcher - now!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 'The breastplate stretcher'?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How long before he figures it out?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Maybe you should have one invented. - All right, all right.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You watch me out there. I still know how to point a lance.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You've no business jousting. Leave that for the young men.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why, because I'm king? Piss on that. I want to hit somebody!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And who's going to hit you back? - Anybody who can.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And the last man in his saddle... - Will be you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There's not a man in the Seven Kingdoms would risk hurting you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Are you telling me those cowards would let me win?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Aye.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Drink. - I'm not thirsty.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Drink. Your king commands it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Gods,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: too fat for my armour.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your squire - a Lannister boy?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Mm. A bloody idiot,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but Cersei insisted.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I have Jon Arryn to thank for her.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 'Cersei Lannister will make a good match,' he told me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 'You'll need her father on your side.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I thought being king meant I could do whatever I wanted.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Enough of this. Let's go watch 'em ride.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: At least I can smell someone else's blood.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Robert. - What?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: An inspiring sight for the people, eh?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Come, bow before your king! Bow, you shits!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Where's Arya? - At her dancing lessons.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Knight of the Flowers.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Thank you, Ser Loras.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Don't let Ser Gregor hurt him.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Hey. - I can't watch.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A hundred gold dragons on the Mountain.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll take that bet. - Now what will I buy with 100 gold dragons?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A dozen barrels of Dornish wine?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Or a girl from the pleasure houses of Lys?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Or you could even buy a friend. - He's going to die.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ser Loras rides well.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Such a shame, Littlefinger.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It would have been so nice for you to have a friend.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And tell me, Lord Renly,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: when will you be having your friend?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Loras knew his mare was in heat. Quite crafty, really.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ser Loras would never do that.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There's no honour in tricks. - No honour and quite a bit of gold.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sword!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Leave him be!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Stop this madness in the name of your king!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Let him go!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I owe you my life, ser.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm no ser.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Remove his hood.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: On that eve, the captive Imp...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Downwards from his horse did limp...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No more would he preen and primp...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: In garb of red and gold...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: This isn't the Kingsroad.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You said we were riding for Winterfell. - I did... Often and loudly.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Very wise. They'll be out in droves,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: looking for me in the wrong place.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Word's probably gotten to my father by now.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He'll be offering a handsome reward.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Everyone knows a Lannister always pays his debts.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Would you be so good as to untie me?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And why would I do that? - Why not?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Am I going to run? The hill tribes would kill me for my boots.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Unless a shadowcat ate me first.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Shadowcats and hill tribes are the least of your concerns.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ah, the eastern road.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We're going to the Vale.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're taking me to your sister's to answer for my imagined crimes.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Tell me, Lady Stark, when was the last time you saw your sister?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Five years ago. - She's changed.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: She was always a bit touched, but now... You might as well kill me here.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I am not a murderer, Lannister. - Neither am I.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I had nothing to do with the attempt on your son's life.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The dagger found... - What sort of imbecile

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: arms an assassin with his own blade?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Should I gag him? - Why?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Am I starting to make sense?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Rodrik!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My lady, this way.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Untie me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If I die, what's the point?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ah!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Rodrik? - I'll be fine, my lady.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There's no need to bloody yourself.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your first?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You need a woman.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Nothing like a woman after a fight.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm willing if she is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Bran.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Iron Islands. Sigil - a kraken.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Words - 'We do not sow.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lords? - The Greyjoys.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Famed for their skills at archery, navigation and lovemaking.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And failed rebellions.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sigil - a stag, a crowned stag now that Robert's king.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Good. - Words - 'Ours is the fury.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lords - the Baratheons. - Mm-hm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Westerlands.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sigil - a lion. - Mmm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Words - 'A Lannister always pays his debts.' - No.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A common saying, but not their official motto.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lords - the Lannisters.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We're still on their words. - I don't know them.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You do know them. Think.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 'Unbowed, unbent, unbroken.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: That's House Martell. - 'Righteous in wrath.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: House Hornwood. - 'Family, duty, honour.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Those are Tully words - your mother's.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Are we playing a game? - Family, duty, honour...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is that the right order? - You know it is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Family comes first?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your mother had to leave Winterfell to protect the family.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How can she protect the family

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: if she's not with her family?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your mother sat by your bed

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: for three weeks while you slept.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And then she left!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: When you were born, I was the one who pulled you from your mother.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I placed you in her arms.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: From that moment until the moment she dies,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: she will love you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Absolutely.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Fiercely. - Why did she leave?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I still can't tell you,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but she will be home soon. - Do you know where she is now?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Today?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No, I don't. - Then how can you promise me

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: she'll be home soon?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sometimes I worry you're too smart for your own good.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll never shoot another arrow.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And where is that written?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You need legs to work a bow. - Hmm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If the saddle Lord Tyrion designed actually works,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: you could learn to shoot a bow from horseback.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Really?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Dothraki boys learn when they're four years old.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why shouldn't you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Shh, keep it down.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're not supposed to be inside the castle walls.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I thought you were supposed to be an important person around here.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Important enough for the likes of you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're not the only nobleman in my life, you know.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Who, the Imp? I'd call him half a nobleman.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Jealous?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why should I be jealous?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Anyone with a few coppers in his pocket can own you for the night.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What's a dwarf like down below?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've always wondered.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Might surprise you. - Hmm?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's good with his fingers too. And his tongue.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Generous tipper.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I guess gold is cheap for a Lannister.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You are jealous.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm a Greyjoy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We've been lords of the Iron Islands for 300 years.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There's not a family in Westeros that can look down on us,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: not even the Lannisters.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And what about the Starks?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've been Lord Stark's ward since I was eight years old.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A ward - that's a nice word for it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your father rebelled against King Robert and if he does it again...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My father fought for the freedom of his people.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What did your father do? Fucked a cook and whelped a whore.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're a very serious boy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm not a boy. - Oh, yes, you are.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A serious boy with a serious cock.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I don't want to pay for it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Then get yourself a wife.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Come on.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm not gonna hurt you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How is your son, my lord?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He'll never walk again.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But his mind is sound?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: So they say.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A blessing, then.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I suffered an early mutilation myself.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Some doors close forever...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: others open in most unexpected places.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: May I?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If the wrong ears heard what I'm about to tell you,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: off comes my head.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And who would mourn poor Varys then?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: North or South, they sing no songs for spiders.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But there are things you must know.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You are the King's Hand and the king is a fool -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: your friend, I know, but a fool - and doomed unless you save him.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've been in the capital a month.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why have you waited so long to tell me this?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I didn't trust you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: So why do you trust me now?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The queen is not the only one who has been watching you closely.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There are few men of honour in the capital.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You are one of them.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I would like to believe I am another, strange as that may seem.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What sort of doom does the king face?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The same sort as Jon Arryn.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The tears of lys, they call it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A rare and costly thing,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: as clear and tasteless as water. It leaves no trace.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Who gave it to him?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Some dear friend, no doubt. But which one?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There were many. Lord Arryn was a kind and trusting man.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There was one boy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: All he was he owed to Jon Arryn.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The squire, Ser Hugh?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Pity, what happened to him,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: just when his life seemed to be going so nicely.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If Ser Hugh poisoned him...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: who paid Ser Hugh?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Someone who could afford it. - Jon was a man of peace.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He was Hand for 17 years - 17 good years.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why kill him?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He started asking questions.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's found one bastard already.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He has the book.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The rest will come.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And when he knows the truth, what will he do?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The gods alone know.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The fools tried to kill his son.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What's worse - they botched it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The wolf and the lion will be at each other's throats.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We will be at war soon, my friend. - What good is war now?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We're not ready.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If one Hand can die, why not a second?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: This Hand is not the other.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We need time.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Khal Drogo will not make his move until his son is born.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You know what these savages are. - 'Delay,' you say.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 'Move fast,' I reply.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: This is no longer a game for two players.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It never was.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The first to arrive and the last to leave.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I admire your industry.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You do move quietly.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We all have our qualities.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You look a bit lonely today.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You should pay a visit to my brothel this evening.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: First boy is on the house. - I think you're mistaking

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: business with pleasure. - Am I?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: All those birds that whisper in your ear - such pretty little things.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Trust me,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: we accommodate all inclinations.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, I'm sure. Lord Redwyne likes his boys very young, I hear.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm a purveyor of beauty and discretion - both equally important.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Though I suppose beauty is a subjective quality, no?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is it true that Ser Marlon of Tumblestone prefers amputees?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: All desires are valid to a man with a full purse.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And I heard the most awful rumour about a certain lord

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: with a taste for fresh cadavers.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Must be enormously difficult to accommodate that inclination.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The logistics alone...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: to find beautiful corpses before they rot.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Strictly speaking, such a thing would not be in accordance with the king's laws.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Strictly speaking.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Tell me. Does someone somewhere keep your balls in a little box?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've often wondered.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do you know, I have no idea where they are.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And we had been so close.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But enough about me. How have you been

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: since we last saw each other?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Since you last saw me or since I last saw you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Now the last time I saw you, you were talking to the Hand of the King.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Saw me with your own eyes? - Eyes I own.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Council business.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We all have so much to discuss with Ned Stark.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Everyone's well aware of your enduring fondness for Lord Stark's wife.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If the Lannisters were behind the attempt on the Stark boy's life

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: and it was discovered that you helped the Starks come to that conclusion...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: to think a simple word to the queen...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: One shudders at the thought. - Ooh.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But you know something? I do believe that I have seen you

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: even more recently than you have seen me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Have you? - Yes.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Earlier today, I distinctly recall

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: seeing you talking to Lord Stark in his chambers.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Was that you under the bed?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And not long after that

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: when I saw you escorting a certain

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: foreign dignitary...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Council business?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Of course, you would have friends from across the Narrow Sea.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're from there yourself, after all.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We're friends, aren't we, Lord Varys?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'd like to think we are.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: So you can imagine my burden,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: wondering if the king might question my friend's sympathies.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: To stand at a crossroads where turning left means loyalty to a friend,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: turning right loyalty to the realm...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, please. - To find myself in a position

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: where a simple word to the king...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What are you two conspiring about?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Well, whatever it is, you'd best hurry up.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My brother is coming. - To a small council meeting?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Disturbing news from far away.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Hadn't you heard?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Off with you. No begging.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm not a beggar. I live here.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: D'you want a smack on your ear to help you with your hearing?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I want to see my father.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I want to fuck the queen, for all the good it does me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You want your father, boy?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's lying on the floor of some tavern, getting pissed on by his friends.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My father is Hand of the King!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm not a boy. I'm Arya Stark of Winterfell.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And if you lay a hand on me, my father will have both your heads on spikes.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Now are you going to let me by or do I need to smack you

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: on the ear to help with your hearing?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You know I had half my guard out searching for you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You promised me this would stop. - They said they were going to kill you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Who did? - I didn't see them,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but I think one was fat. - Oh, Arya.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm not lying! They said you found the bastard

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: and the wolves are fighting the lions and the savage...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Something about the savage.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Where did you hear this? - In the dungeons,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: near the dragon skulls. - What were you doing in the dungeons?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Chasing a cat.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Pardon, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There's a night's watchman here begging a word. Says it's urgent.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your name, friend? - Yoren, if it please.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: This must be your son. He has the look. - I'm a girl!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Did Benjen send you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No one sent me, my lord. I'm here to find men for the Wall,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: see if there's any scum in the dungeons that might be fit for service.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, we'll find recruits for you. - Thank you, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But that's not why I disturb you now.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your brother Benjen, his blood runs black -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: makes him as much my brother as yours.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It's for his sake I rode here so hard I damn near killed my horse.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: There are others riding too.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The whole city will know by tomorrow.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Know what?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Best said in private, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Go on. We'll talk more later.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Jory, take her safely to her room.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Come along, my lady. You heard your father.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How many guards does my father have? - Here in King's Landing? Fifty.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You wouldn't let anyone kill him, would you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No fear on that count, little lady.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Well? - It's about your wife, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: She's taken the Imp.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're far from home, Lady Stark.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: To whom do I speak? - Ser Vardis Egan, knight of the Vale.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is Lady Arryn expecting your visit? - There was no time to send word.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: May I ask, my lady,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: why he is with you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: That's why there was no time.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He is my prisoner. - He doesn't look like a prisoner.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My sister will decide what he looks like.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Yes, my lady. She will at that.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Eyrie. They say it's impregnable.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Give me ten good men and some climbing spikes,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll impregnate the bitch.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I like you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lord Stark, your presence has been requested

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: in the small council chamber. A meeting has been called.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I need to see the king first - alone.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The king is at the small council meeting, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He has summoned you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is it about my wife? - No, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I believe it concerns Daenerys Targaryen.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The whore is pregnant. - You're speaking of murdering a child.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I warned you this would happen, back in the North.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I warned you, but you didn't care to hear.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Well, hear it now.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I want 'em dead, mother and child both.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And that fool Viserys as well.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is that plain enough for you? I want them both dead.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You will dishonour yourself forever if you do this.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Honour?! I've got seven kingdoms to rule!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: One king, seven kingdoms.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do you think honour keeps them in line?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do you think it's honour that's keeping the peace?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It's fear - fear and blood. - Then we're no better than the Mad King.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Careful, Ned. Careful now. - You want to assassinate a girl

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: because the spider heard a rumour?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No rumour, my lord. The princess is with child.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Based on whose information? - Ser Jorah Mormont.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He is serving as advisor to the Targaryens.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Mormont? You bring us the whispers

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: of a traitor half a world away and call it fact?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Jorah Mormont's a slaver, not a traitor.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Small difference, I know, to an honourable man.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He broke the law, betrayed his family, fled our land.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We commit murder on the word of this man?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And if he's right? If she has a son?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A Targaryen at the head of a Dothraki army -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: what then? - The Narrow Sea still lies between us.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll fear the Dothraki the day they teach their horses to run on water.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do nothing?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: That's your wise advice?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do nothing till our enemies are on our shores?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're my council. Counsel!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Speak sense to this honourable fool.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I understand your misgivings, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Truly, I do. It is a terrible thing

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: we must consider, a vile thing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Yet we who presume to rule

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: must sometimes do vile things

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: for the good of the realm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Should the gods grant Daenerys a son,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: the realm will bleed. - I bear this girl no ill will,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but should the Dothraki invade, how many innocents will die?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How many towns will burn?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is it not wiser, kinder even,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: that she should die now so that tens of thousands might live?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We should have had them both killed years ago.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: When you find yourself in bed with an ugly woman,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: best close your eyes, get it over with.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Cut her throat. Be done with it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I followed you into war -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: twice,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: without doubts,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: without second thoughts.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But I will not follow you now.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Robert I grew up with

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: didn't tremble at the shadow of an unborn child.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: She dies.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I will have no part in it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're the King's Hand, Lord Stark.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You'll do as I command or I'll find me a Hand who will.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And good luck to him.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I thought you were a better man. - Out. Out, damn you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm done with you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Go, run back to Winterfell!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll have your head on a spike!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll put it there myself, you fool!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You think you're too good for this?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Too proud and honourable? This is a war!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll go ahead with my daughters. Get them ready. Do it yourself.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Don't ask anyone for help. - Right away, my lord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lord Baelish is here for you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: His Grace went on about you at some length

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: after you took your leave. The word 'treason' was mentioned.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What can I do for you? - When do you return to Winterfell?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why? What do you care? - If you're still here come nightfall,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll take you to see the last person Jon Arryn spoke with before falling ill.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If that sort of thing still interests you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I don't have the time.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It won't take more than an hour. But as you please.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Round up all the men we have and station them outside the girls' chambers.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Who are your best two swords? - Heward and Wyl.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Find them and meet me at the stables.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You bring him here without permission?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You pollute my home with his presence?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your aunt has done a bad thing, Robin, a very bad thing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You remember her, don't you?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Isn't he beautiful?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And strong too. Jon knew it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: His last words were 'The seed is strong.'

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He wanted everyone to know what a good, strong boy

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: his son would grow up to be.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Look at him, the lord of all the Vale.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lysa,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: you wrote me about the Lannisters,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: warning me... - To stay away from them!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Not to bring one here!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Mummy...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: is that the bad man? - It is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's little.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's Tyrion the Imp, of House Lannister.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He killed your father. He murdered the Hand of the King!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, did I kill him too?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've been a very busy man. - You will watch your tongue!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: These men are knights of the Vale.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Every one of them loved Jon Arryn.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Every one of them would die for me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If any harm comes to me, my brother Jaime will see that they do.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You can't hurt us. No one can hurt us here. Tell him, Mummy!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Tell him! - Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh, my sweet boy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's just trying to frighten us. Lannisters are all liars.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No one will hurt my baby.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Mummy...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I want to see the bad man fly.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Perhaps you will, my little love. - This man is my prisoner.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I will not have him harmed.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ser Vardis,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: my sister's guest is weary.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Take him down below so he can rest.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Introduce him to Mord.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You go sleep, dwarf man.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sleep good, little dwarf man!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Lord Stark's lucky he still has a head.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Robert will rant for a few days, but he won't do anything.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He adores the man. - You're jealous.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Are you sure this won't hurt? - Only if I slip.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And you'd prefer me like this? - Mm-hm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If you want hairless, maybe you should find a little boy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I want you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My brother thinks that anyone who hasn't been to war isn't a man.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He treats me as if I'm a spoilt child.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, and you're not?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Loras Tyrell, the Knight of the Flowers?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How many wars have you fought in?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh, and how much did your father spend on that armour of yours?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Hold still.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: All I ever hear from Robert and Stannis is how I'm not tough enough,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: how I squirm at the sight of blood.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You did vomit when that boy's eye was knocked out in the melee.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: His eye was dangling out of the damn socket!

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He shouldn't have entered the melee if he didn't know how to fight.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Easy for you to say. Not everyone is such a gifted swordsman.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It's not a gift. No one gave it to me.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm good because I work at it -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: every day of my life since I could hold a stick.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I could work at fighting all day, every day, I'd still never be as good as you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Yes, well, I guess we'll never know.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Everywhere? - Everywhere.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: So how did it end up?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Targaryen girl will die? - It needs to be done, unpleasant as it is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Robert's rather tasteless about it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Every time he talks about killing her, I swear the table rises six inches.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: It's a shame he can't muster the same enthusiasm for his wife.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He does have a deep, abiding lust for her money.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You have to give it to the Lannisters - they may be

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: the most pompous, ponderous cunts the gods ever suffered to walk the world,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but they do have outrageous amounts of money.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I have an outrageous amount of money. - Not as much as the Lannisters.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But a lot more than you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Robert's threatening to take me hunting with him.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Last time we were out there for two weeks.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Tramping through the trees in the rain, day after day,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: all so he can stick his spear into something's flesh.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Oh. But Robert loves his killing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And he's the king. - Hmm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How did that ever happen? - Because he loves his killing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And he used to be good at it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Do you know who should be king?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Be serious. - I am.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: My father could be your bank.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I've never fought in a war before,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but I'd fight for you. - I'm fourth in line.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And where's Robert in the line of royal succession?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Joffrey is a monster. Tommen is eight.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Stannis? - Stannis has the personality of a lobster.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's still my older brother.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What are you doing?! - Look at it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You cut me. - It's just blood. We've all got it in us.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sometimes a little spills.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: If you become king, you're going to see a lot of this.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You need to get used to it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Go on. Look.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: People love you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They love to serve you because you're kind to them.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They want to be near you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You're willing to do what needs to be done,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: but you don't gloat over it.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You don't love killing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Where is it written that power is the sole province of the worst?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: That thrones are only made for the hated and the feared?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You would be a wonderful king.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm sorry your marriage to Ned Stark didn't work out.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You seemed so good together.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'm glad I could do something to make you happy.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Without a Hand, everything will fall to pieces.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I suppose this is where you tell me to give the job to your brother Jaime.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: No.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: He's not serious enough.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I'll say this for Ned Stark - he's serious enough.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Hmm.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Was it really worth it? Losing him this way?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I don't know.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: But I do know this -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: if the Targaryen girl convinces her horselord husband to invade

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: and the Dothraki horde crosses the Narrow Sea...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: we won't be able to stop them.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: The Dothraki don't sail. Every child knows that.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They don't have discipline. They don't have armour.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They don't have siege weapons. - It's a neat little trick you do -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: you move your lips and your father's voice comes out.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Is my father wrong?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Let's say Viserys Targaryen lands

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: with 40,000 Dothraki screamers at his back.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We hole up in our castles.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: A wise move -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: only a fool would meet the Dothraki in an open field.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They leave us in our castles.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: They go from town to town, looting and burning,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: killing every man who can't hide behind a stone wall,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: stealing all our crops and livestock,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: enslaving all our women and children.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How long do the people of the Seven Kingdoms stand behind

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: their absentee king, their cowardly king

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: hiding behind high walls?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: When do the people decide that Viserys Targaryen

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: is the rightful monarch after all?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We still outnumber them.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Which is the bigger number - five or one?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Five.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Five...

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: One.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: One army - a real army

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: united behind one leader with one purpose.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Our purpose died with the Mad King.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Now we've got as many armies

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: as there are men with gold in their purse.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And everybody wants something different.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Your father wants to own the world.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ned Stark wants to run away and bury his head in the snow.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What do you want?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: We haven't had a real fight in nine years.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Backstabbing doesn't prepare you for a fight.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: And that's all the realm is now -

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: backstabbing and scheming

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: and arse-licking and money-grubbing.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Sometimes I don't know what holds it together.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Our marriage.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Ah, so here we sit,

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: 17 years later, holding it all together.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Don't you get tired?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Every day.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: How long can hate hold a thing together?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Well, 17 years is quite a long time.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Yes, it is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Yes, it is.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: What was she like?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: You've never asked about her, not once.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: Why not?

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: At first, just saying her name even in private

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: felt like I was breathing life back into her.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: I thought if I didn't talk about her, she'd just fade away for you.

name: The Wolf and the Lion
cap: When I realised that wasn't going to happen,
