cap: where I would say his name every night before I went to bed.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Willem. Willem.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Willem.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: A prayer almost.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Well, one day,

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Willem came riding back into town.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: I buried an axe so deep into Willem's skull they had to bury him with it.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Willem's horse got me to the Wall and I've been wearing black ever since.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: That'll help you sleep, eh?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Ho!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Get up, you lazy sons of whores!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Arm yourselves.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Get up. - Get up.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Keep out of sight, both of you.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: No, I'm not afraid. - I can fight.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Keep out of sight.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: If things go wrong, you run.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Do you hear me? You run along north and don't look back.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Hey, there's men out there who want to fuck your corpses.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Outside, now!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Come on, move, move!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Gold cloaks!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Everyone out!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Hey, you! Open the damn cage!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Where's the bastard, crow?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Got more than a few bastards here. Who's asking?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Ser Amory Lorch, sworn bannerman to Lord Tywin Lannister.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: These men from the capital requested our assistance.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Drop your weapons in the name of the king.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Now, which king would that be?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: This is your last chance.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: In the name of King Joffrey, drop your weapons.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: I don't think I will.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: So be it.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: I always hated crossbows. Take too long to load.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Boy, come here. Boy!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Sweet boy, help us. - Come back here!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Help us, boy!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: A man can fight! Free us!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Quick, give it to me.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Give me the axe. Give me that.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Put them on the wagon!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: There's more here. Come on.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: What do we have here?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: No!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: That's a fine little blade.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Maybe I'll pick my teeth with it.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: I yield! I yield!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Round up any survivors.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: We'll take them back to Harrenhal.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: You heard him. You're coming with us.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: I yield!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Help!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Help me!

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Something wrong with your leg, boy?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Look at it.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Can you walk?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: No. You got to carry me.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: All right.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: 'Carry him,' he says.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: We're looking for a bastard named Gendry.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: Give him up

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: or I'll start taking eyeballs.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: You want Gendry?

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: You already got him.

name: What Is Dead May Never Die
cap: He loved that helmet.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It's got to be the Mountain. He's the biggest.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He's the strongest. - Bulls are bigger than lions.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Doesn't mean I'd pick a bull in a fight.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If the bull had fangs and claws, I would.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Right, the Mountain or our man Jaime.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If he ever gets out.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Loras Tyrell?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Loras Tyrell. He's prettier than the queen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't care about pretty. He's better with a sword than any of them.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: How good could he be?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He's been stabbing Renly Baratheon for years, and Renly ain't dead.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The horses seem a little spooked to you?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They're horses.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They get spooked by their own shadows.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do you hear that?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: There's something out there.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, you're a right little prick.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You should see your face.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I swear you pissed yourself.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: 'Oh, who goes there? Ahh!'

name: Garden of Bones
cap: There is something out there.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Yeah, don't even try me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Rennick. - Do you think I'm an idiot?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Rennick!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: King in the North! - The King in the North!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Five Lannisters dead for every one of ours.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They're dead. Take everything they've got.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We've nowhere to keep all these prisoners.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Barely enough food to feed our own.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We're not executing prisoners, Lord Bolton.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Of course, Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The officers will be useful.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Some of them may be privy to Tywin Lannister's plans.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I doubt it.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Well, we'll learn soon enough.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: In my family, we say, 'A naked man has few secrets.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: 'A flayed man none.'

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My father outlawed flaying in the North.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We're not in the North. - We're not torturing them.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The high road's very pretty,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but you'll have a hard time marching your army down it.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Lannisters hold prisoners of their own.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I won't give them an excuse to abuse my sisters.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, don't! Don't! Please!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The rot's set in.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, don't! No, don't!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Shh. - Please, don't!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It'll get better. It doesn't even hurt.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The rot will spread. If we don't take the foot now...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, you can't!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ser! Please, ser.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I can't lose... - You'll die if she doesn't.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't want to be a cripple, please.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Surely one of our men needs your attention more than this cub.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your men are not my men, my lord.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Put this in your mouth and lie down. You don't want to watch.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No! You can't! - Bite on it.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It's better than biting your own tongue, believe me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What's your name? - Talisa.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your last name?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You want to know what side my family fights on?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You know my family name. You have me at a disadvantage.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That boy lost his foot on your orders.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They killed my father.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That boy did? - The family he fights for.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do you think he's friends with King Joffrey?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He's a fisherman's son that grew up near Lannisport.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He probably never held a spear before they shoved one in his hands a few months ago.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I have no hatred for the lad.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That should help his foot grow back.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You'd have us surrender, end all this bloodshed.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I understand. The country would be at peace

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and life would be just under the righteous hand of good King Joffrey.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You're going to kill Joffrey? - If the gods give me strength.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And then what? - I don't know.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We'll go back to Winterfell.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I have no desire to sit on the Iron Throne.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: So who will?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't know.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You're fighting to overthrow a king,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and yet you have no plan for what comes after?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: First we have to win the war.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You never told me where you're from.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Volantis. - Volantis? You're far from home.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The boy was lucky you were here.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He was unlucky that you were.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You're here to answer for your brother's latest treasons.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: whatever my traitor brother has done, I had no part.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You know that. I beg you, please...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ser Lancel, tell her of this outrage.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Using some vile sorcery,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: your brother fell on Stafford Lannister with an army of wolves.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Thousands of good men were butchered.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: After the slaughter, the Northmen feasted on the flesh of the slain.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Killing you would send your brother a message.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But my mother insists on keeping you alive.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Stand.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: So we'll have to send your brother a message some other way.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Meryn.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Leave her face. I like her pretty.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Meryn, my lady is overdressed.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Unburden her.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If you want Robb Stark to hear us, we're going to have to speak louder.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What is the meaning of this?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What kind of knight beats a helpless girl?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The kind who serves his king, Imp.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Careful, now. We don't want to get blood all over your pretty white cloak.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Someone get the girl something to cover herself with.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She is to be your queen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Have you no regard for her honour?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm punishing her. - For what crimes?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She did not fight her brother's battle, you half-wit.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You can't talk to me like that. The king can do as he likes!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Mad King did as he liked.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Has your Uncle Jaime ever told you what happened to him?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No one threatens His Grace in the presence of the Kingsguard.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm not threatening the king, ser. I am educating my nephew.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Bronn, the next time Ser Meryn speaks, kill him.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That was a threat. See the difference?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I apologise for my nephew's behaviour.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Tell me the truth. Do you want an end to this engagement?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am loyal to King Joffrey, my one true love.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Lady Stark, you may survive us yet.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The little king's backed up.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Clogged from balls to brains.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You think dipping his wick will cure what ails him?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: There's no cure for being a cunt.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But the boy's at that age.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And he's got nothing to do all day but pick wings off flies.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Couldn't hurt to get some of the poison out.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What are you doing here, dog?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your uncle left your nameday present and asked me to see that you got it.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What is it?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Look inside, Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Happy nameday, Your Grace. - My nameday has passed.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We won't tell if you won't.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Her.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Touch her.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Could you hit her?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My uncle sent you?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Yes, Your Grace. He chose us himself.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Hmm.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Use this.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Harder.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I said harder.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He'd want me to get his money's worth.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace, too much pain will spoil the pleasure.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Please, Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace, if your uncle finds out...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, I want him to find out.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You will bring her to his chambers when you're finished

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and show him what you've done,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: or the same thing will happen to you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Begin.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Harder!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Well, if it isn't my favourite whoremonger.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Pray I haven't kept you waiting long.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Now you do the Lannisters' bidding, is that it?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Tell me, was my brother's body even cold before you secured your newest patron?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm a practical man.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Just not a loyal one.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And who would you have me be loyal to?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your brother's corpse?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't like you, Lord Baelish.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't like your face.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't like the words that come oozing out of your mouth.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't want you in my tent one minute more than necessary.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: So tell me, why are you here?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You can trust Brienne. Her loyalty comes without charge.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You still have many friends at court, Your Grace,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: many who believe Ned Stark erred by not supporting your claim.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Now I understand.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You know I have the numbers. You know I'm marching on King's Landing.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: When I take the throne, you hope to retain your position.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And your head.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I would give priority to my head.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I understand that you don't like me, and while that saddens me greatly,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I did not come here today seeking your affection.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: When you march on King's Landing,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: you may find yourself facing a protracted siege or...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: open gates.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Lord Baelish.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: All of these tents look the same to me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Would you be so kind... - It would be my pleasure.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It took me weeks to learn my way around the camp.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Twice I walked in on officers in stages of undress.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And the moment I learn which tent is mine, we're on the move again.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: 'Your tent'?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Not 'Our tent'?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The king snores, perhaps? Or simply prefers solitude?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Pressures of command, no doubt.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Four kings vying for the throne.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am not tutored in warfare,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but basic arithmetic favours the side with the greater numbers.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If war were arithmetic, the mathematicians would rule the world.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I did notice your brother entering His Grace's tent just now.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The place of a Kingsguard is by the king's side.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And on the night of your wedding, who was by the king's side then?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You seem quite interested in our marriage.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your marriage is quite interesting.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Not only to me, but to the realm.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The marriage of a wealthy girl always breeds interest, if nothing else.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You've never married, have you?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I've been unlucky in my affections, sadly.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That is sad.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Though perhaps it's for the best.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The whole notion of marriage seems to confuse you,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: so allow me to explain.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My husband is my king, and my king is my husband.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Here is your tent, Lord Baelish. Good night.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: This isn't your horse.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It was given to me by the Thirteen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Elders of Qarth.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Qarth?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Three days to the east, on the sea.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Will they let us in?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They said they would be honoured to receive the Mother of Dragons.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What do you know of this place?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Only that the desert around their walls is called the Garden of Bones.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Every time the Qartheen shut their gates on a traveller,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: the garden grows.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Go on! - You, keep moving!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Bring her about!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What kind of fire melts stone?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Dragon fire.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: There's dragons here?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, all the dragons are dead.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What's that smell?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Dead people.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Move.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Please, please, no, no!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He's dead.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He was my son.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My sister was three days ago.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My husband, the day before that.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They take someone every day?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Does anyone live?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Joffrey.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cersei.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ilyn Payne.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Hound.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Joffrey.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cersei.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ilyn Payne.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Hound.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Joffrey. Cersei.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ilyn Payne. The Hound.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: How dare you?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You may have heard false reports.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You betrayed Ned. - Betrayed?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I wanted him to serve as Protector of the Realm.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I begged him to seize the moment.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I trusted you. My husband trusted you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And you repaid our faith with treachery.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, my lady. - Get out!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cat, I've...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I've loved you since I was a boy.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It seems to me that fate has given us this chance...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Have you lost your mind? Get out!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do you want to see your girls again?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Sansa, more beautiful than ever?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And Arya, just as wild as ever?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You have Arya, too?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Both girls are healthy and safe.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: For now.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But you know the queen and you know Joffrey.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I fear for their longevity if they remain in the capital.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What do you want?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Lannisters will trade your daughters for the Kingslayer.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Of course they will.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Jaime Lannister for two girls?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Robb will never agree to those terms.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm not bringing these terms to him.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm bringing them to you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You think I keep secrets from my son?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Robb has surprised them all with his skills in battle,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but he's not a mother.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Consider it, Cat.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You may not get another chance.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I've brought you a gift. - I don't want your gifts.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: A token of Tyrion Lannister's goodwill.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He wants you to understand that this exchange of prisoners

name: Garden of Bones
cap: is offered in good faith.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Good faith?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What's this?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your husband was an honourable man.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He should rest beside his family in the crypts beneath Winterfell.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You may not believe... - Get out.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Get up, you dogs!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That's him, the one who picks.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Mountain.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What are you doing?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He told me he stares at him every day.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: That's why he doesn't get picked.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Move, boy!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Move!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Is there gold and silver in the village?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't know. - Gems?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I didn't see any.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Where is the Brotherhood? - I don't know.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Where is the Brotherhood? - I don't know. Please.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Where is the Brotherhood? - I don't know.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Which of the villagers aided them?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't know. - Who?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Who? - I never saw.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Who? - I never saw.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Please. Please, stop. Please, it's starting to...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Who? - I didn't see anyone help him.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Take it off! Take it off!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Who helped him? - Ganes, the butcher,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and his son. - That's better.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You've been very helpful. - No, stop, please!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What are you doing? Please, stop!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Please, stop! No! No!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I told you everything! No!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Joffrey.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cersei.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ilyn Payne. The Hound.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Please, Polliver. Some food.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Just a crust of bread.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Polliver.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Mountain.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Lady Stark, I had not thought to find you in the Stormlands.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I had not thought to be here, Lord Stannis.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Can that truly be you? - Who else might it be?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: When I saw your standard, I couldn't be sure.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Whose banner is that? - My own.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I suppose if we used the same one, the battle would be terribly confusing.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Why is your stag on fire?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The king has taken for his sigil the fiery heart of the Lord of Light.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ah, you must be this fire priestess we hear so much about.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Mmm, brother,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: now I understand why you found religion in your old age.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Watch yourself, Renly.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, no, I'm relieved.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I never really believed you were a fanatic.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Charmless, rigid, a bore, yes,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but not a godly man.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You should kneel before your brother.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He's the Lord's chosen,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: born amidst salt and smoke.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Born amidst salt and smoke?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Is he a ham? - That's twice I've warned you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Listen to yourselves.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If you were sons of mine, I would knock your heads together

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and lock you in a bedchamber until you remembered that you were brothers.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It is strange to find you beside my brother, Lady Stark.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your husband was a supporter of my claim.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Lord Eddard's integrity cost him his head.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And you sit beside this pretender and chastise me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We share a common enemy.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Iron Throne is mine by right.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: All those that deny that are my foes.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The whole realm denies it, from Dorne to the Wall.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Old men deny it with their death rattle

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and unborn children deny it in their mother's wombs.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No one wants you for their king.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You never wanted any friends, brother.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But a man without friends is a man without power.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: For the sake of the mother who bore us, I will give you this one night to reconsider.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Strike your banners, come to me before dawn,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and I will grant you your old seat in the Council.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'll even name you my heir

name: Garden of Bones
cap: until a son is born to me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Otherwise I shall destroy you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Look across those fields, brother.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Can you see all those banners?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You think a few bolts of cloth will make you king?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The men holding those bolts of cloth will make me king.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We shall see, Renly.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Come the dawn, we shall see.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Look to your sins, Lord Renly.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The night is dark and full of terrors.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Would you believe I loved him once?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I thought we were welcome.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If you heard a Dothraki horde was approaching your city,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: you might do the same, Khaleesi.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Horde?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My name is Daenerys...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Daenerys Stormborn of the house Targaryen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You know me, my lord?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Only by reputation, Khaleesi.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And I'm no lord, merely a humble merchant.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They call you the Mother of Dragons.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And what should I call you?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, my name is quite long

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and quite impossible for foreigners to pronounce.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am simply a trader of spices.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But we are the Thirteen,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: charged with the governance and protection of Qarth,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: the greatest city that ever was or will be.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The beauty of Quarth is legendary... - Qarth.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Qarth.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Might we see the dragons?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My friend,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: we have travelled very far.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We have no food, no water.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Once I see my people fed, I would be honoured...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Forgive me, Mother of Dragons,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but no man alive has seen a living dragon.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Some of my more sceptical friends

name: Garden of Bones
cap: refuse to believe your children

name: Garden of Bones
cap: even exist.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: All we ask is the chance to see for ourselves.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am not a liar.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, I don't think you are.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But as I've never met you before,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: my opinion on the matter is of limited value.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Where I come from,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: guests are treated with respect, not insulted at the gates.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Then perhaps you should return to where you come from.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We wish you well.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What are you doing?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You promised to receive me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We have received you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Here we are, and here you are.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If you do not let us in, all of us will die.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Which we shall deeply regret.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But Qarth did not become the greatest city that ever was or will be

name: Garden of Bones
cap: by letting Dothraki savages through its gates.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Khaleesi, please be careful.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Thirteen!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: When my dragons are grown, we will take back what was stolen from me

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and destroy those who have wronged me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: We will lay waste to armies and burn cities to the ground.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Turn us away and we will burn you first.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ah.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You are a true Targaryen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Only, as you said a moment ago,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: if we don't let you into the city, you will all die.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And so...

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Retreating in fear from a little girl is unbecoming of the greatest city

name: Garden of Bones
cap: that ever was or will be.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The discussion is over, Xaro Xhoan Daxos.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Thirteen have spoken.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am one of the Thirteen,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and I am still speaking.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The girl threatens to burn our city to the ground

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and you would invite her in for a cup of wine?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She is the Mother of Dragons.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do you expect her to watch her people starve without breathing fire?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I believe we can allow a few Dothraki

name: Garden of Bones
cap: through our gates without dooming our city.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: After all, here I am,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: a savage from the Summer Isles, and Qarth still stands.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Our decision is final.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Very well.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I invoke soumai.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I will vouch for her, her people, and her dragons, in accordance with the law.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Be it on your head.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Welcome to Qarth, my lady.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Is there gold or silver in the village?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm not from the village. - Where is the Brotherhood?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I don't know what that is.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You two. Take Lord Lannister's things to his quarters.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What's this?

cap: We weren't expecting you till tomorrow, Lord Tywin.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Evidently not.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Why are these prisoners not in their cells?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cells are overflowing, my lord.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: This lot won't be here long. Don't need no permanent place.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: After we interrogate 'em, we usually just...

cap: Are we so well-manned that we can afford to discard

name: Garden of Bones
cap: able young bodies and skilled labourers?

cap: You, do you have a trade?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Smith, my lord.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What are you looking at? Kneel!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Kneel or I'll carve your lungs out, boy.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: He'll do no such thing.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: This one's a girl, you idiot,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: dressed as a boy.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Why? - Safer to travel, my lord.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Smart.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: More than I can say for this lot.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Get these prisoners to work.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Bring the girl.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I need a new cupbearer.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My lord.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your visits are too few, cousin.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Her Grace, the Queen Regent,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: commands you to release Grand Maester Pycelle.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Here's your warrant. - So it is.

cap: Will you take a cup with me?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I find that mulled wine helps me sleep.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am here at Her Grace's behest, not to drink with you, Imp.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If my sister was so concerned for Pycelle,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I would have thought she'd come herself.

cap: I don't care what you make of it,

name: Garden of Bones

cap: And you've received these instructions directly from Cersei?

cap: As I said several times.

cap: And you've waited this long to deliver the information?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: When the Queen Regent gives me a command, I carry it out without delay.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cersei must have great trust in you,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: allowing you into her chamber during the hour of the wolf.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The Queen Regent has a great many responsibilities.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She often works from dusk till dawn.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She must be very glad to have you helping her from dusk till dawn.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Ah.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Lavender oil.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: She always loved lavender oil, even as a girl.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am a knight!

name: Garden of Bones
cap: An anointed knight, yes.

cap: Tell me, did Cersei have you knighted before or after she took you into her bed?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: What? Nothing to say?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No more warnings for me, ser?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You will withdraw these filthy accusations.

cap: Have you ever given any thought to what King Joffrey will have to say

cap: It's not my fault!

cap: Did she take you against your will?

cap: Can you not defend yourself, knight?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your own father, Lord Tywin, when I was named the king's squire,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: he told me to obey her in everything.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Did he tell you to fuck her, too?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I only meant I did as I was bid.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Hated every moment of it,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: is that what you'll have me believe?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: A high place in court, a knighthood,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: my sister's legs spreading open for you at night.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, yes, it must have been terrible.

cap: Wait here. His Grace will want to hear this.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Mercy! Mercy, my lord! I beg you. - Save it for Joffrey. He loves a good grovel.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My lord, it was your sister's bidding, the queen.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'll leave the city at once, I swear.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No, I think not. - My lord?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You heard me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: My father told you to obey my sister. Obey her.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Stay close to her side. Keep her trust.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Pleasure her whenever she requires.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No one ever need know, as long as you keep faith with me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I want to know what Cersei is doing,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: where she goes, who she sees, what they talk of, everything.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And you will tell me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Yes, my lord, I will.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I swear it, as you command.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, rise, rise.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Let us drink to our understanding.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Oh, you don't have a cup. Oh, well.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Smile, cousin. My sister is a beautiful woman, and it's all for the good of the realm.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Go back and tell her that I beg her forgiveness,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: that I want no more conflict between us

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and that, henceforth, I shall do nothing without her consent.

cap: But her demands?

cap: Oh, I'll give her Pycelle.

cap: You will? - Yes, I'll release him in the morning.

cap: Cersei can keep him as a pet, if she wants, but I will not have him on the Council.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I could swear that I had not harmed a single hair on his head,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but that would not, strictly speaking, be true.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Stay within one table length.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do your knucklebones bring you luck?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Well, life's been good since you hacked them off, Your Grace.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And it's four less fingernails to clean.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Fewer. - Pardon?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Four fewer fingernails to clean.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Never understood why you had to wear them.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It reminds me of where I come from and where I am now.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It reminds me of your justice.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: It was an honest punishment and you were good with the cleaver.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You were a hero and a smuggler.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: A good act does not wash out the bad, nor a bad the good.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: A lesson I've tried to teach my son.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Does he listen? - To me?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Gods, no.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: But if your red woman told him to leap from the crow's nest...

name: Garden of Bones

cap: I trust you've not forgotten your smuggler's tricks.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I've lived within the law for 17...

cap: I want you to be a smuggler this time.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Any shore, any night.

cap: What am I bringing ashore?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: The red woman.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: No one must know what you do and we'll not speak of this again.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I am true to Your Grace and always will be,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: but surely there are other ways, cleaner ways.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Cleaner ways don't win wars.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Are you afraid, Onion Knight?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Someone once told me the night is dark and full of terrors.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You've carried more unpleasant cargo in your time.

cap: Are you a good man, Ser Davos Seaworth?

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'd say my parts are mixed, my lady, good and bad.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: If half an onion is black with rot, it's a rotten onion.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: A man is good or he is evil.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And which are you? - Oh, good.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm a knight myself, of sorts, a champion of light and life.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Well, that must be very nice for you.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Do you love your wife? - I do.

cap: Yet you have known other women.

cap: Don't talk about my wife.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: I'm not. I'm talking about other women.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Like me, Ser Davos.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You want me.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: You want to see what's beneath this robe.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And you will.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Strange that this Lord of Light asks you to work in the shadows.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Shadows cannot live in the dark, Ser Davos.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They are servants of light, the children of fire.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: And the brighter the flame, the darker they are.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: These weren't here before. They've barred the passage.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: They can't bar our passage.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: Gods protect us.

name: Garden of Bones
cap: There's only one god, Ser Davos,

name: Garden of Bones
cap: and he only protects those who serve him.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You swear it? - By the mother.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: My son has no interest in the Iron Throne.

cap: Then I see no reason for hostility between us.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Your son can go on calling himself King in the North.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The Starks will have dominion over all lands north of Moat Cailin,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: provided he swears me an oath of fealty.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And the wording of this oath?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The same Ned Stark swore to Robert 18 years ago.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Cat, their friendship held the kingdoms together.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And in return for my son's loyalty?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: In the morning, I'll destroy my brother's army.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: When that's done,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Baratheon and Stark will fight their common enemy together,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: as they have done many times before.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Our two houses have always been close,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: which is why I am begging you to reconsider this battle.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Negotiate a peace with your brother.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Negotiate with Stannis?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You heard him out there.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I'd have better luck debating the wind.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Please bring my terms to your son.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I believe we are natural allies.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I hope he feels the same.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Together we could end this war in a fortnight.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: No!

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: No.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Follow me!

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You'll die for this. - No, wait, it wasn't her!

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We've got to leave.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: They'll hang you for this.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Now.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I won't leave him.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You can't avenge him if you're dead.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Over there, go!

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Not that way.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We need to go home.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Loras. - My lord, my lady.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Get out.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Stannis will be here in an hour.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: When he arrives, Renly's bannermen will flock to him.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Your former companions will fight for the privilege

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: of selling you to their new king.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And you want that privilege for yourself.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You will note that I am standing here talking to you,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: not Stannis.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: There's no time for this.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Ride back to Highgarden, sister.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I'm not running from Stannis.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Brienne of Tarth murdered Renly.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I don't believe that.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You don't believe that.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Who gained the most from our king's death?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Stannis.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I will put a sword through his righteous face.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You can't stay here.

cap: He would have been a true king,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: a good king.

cap: Tell me, Ser Loras,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: what do you desire most in this world?

cap: Revenge.

cap: I have always found that to be the purest of motivations,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: not today.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You'll be cut to pieces before he sets foot on solid ground.

cap: If it is justice that you want, be smart about it.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You can't avenge him from the grave.

cap: Bring the horses.

cap: Please.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: He was very handsome.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: He was, Your Grace.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: 'Your Grace.'

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Calling yourself king doesn't make you one.

cap: And if Renly wasn't a king, I wasn't a queen.

cap: Do you want to be a queen?

cap: No.

cap: Killed? By whom?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Accounts differ.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Most seem to implicate Catelyn Stark in some way.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Really? Who'd have thought?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Some say it was one of his own Kingsguard,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: while still others say it was Stannis himself who did it

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: after negotiations went sour.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Whomever did it, I say well done.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It's not what Varys says.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: He says Renly's army is flocking to support Stannis,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: which would give Stannis superiority over us on both land and sea.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Littlefinger says we can outspend him three to one.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And I say Father raised you to have too much respect for money.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Stannis Baratheon is coming for us, sooner rather than later.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Aren't there other things you should be doing,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: like sealing my daughter in a crate so you can ship her away?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: She'll be safer in Dorne.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Yes, I know how concerned you are for her safety.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It so happens that I am.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Myrcella is a sweet, innocent girl and I don't blame her at all for you.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: So clever.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Aren't you always so clever with your schemes and your plots?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Schemes and plots are the same thing.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: They are going to attack us.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We need to be ready.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: No need to concern yourself over it.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The king is taking personal charge of siege preparations.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: May I ask specifically what the king has in mind?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You may, specifically, or you may ask vaguely.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The answer will be the same.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It's important that we talk about this.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It's the king's royal prerogative

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: to withhold sensitive information from his councillors.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It's wildfire.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Wildfire?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You wouldn't lie to me, would you, cousin?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: No. - That's a lie right there.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It is not a lie. Why would I lie?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Tell me,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: if the vile allegations against my brother and sister are true,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: do you think it will make Jaime more likely to kill you or less likely?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: When I tell him you're fucking her, I mean.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I'm telling you the truth.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The smart money would be on more likely.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: She's making wildfire.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: But then perhaps his own unnatural urges will give him sympathy for yours.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The Alchemists' Guild is being commissioned.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I suppose there's only one way to find out.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: They have thousands of pots already stored in their vaults.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: They are planning to launch it from the city walls

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: into Stannis' ships and armies.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Please.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: When did she tell you this?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I heard her talking with the pyromancer.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And the other night, after I left her, she went to meet him.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I swear to you.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Swear to me on what?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: On my life.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: But I don't care about your life.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: In the light of the Seven, by all that is holy and right,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I, Lancel Lannister, do solemnly vow...

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: All right, all right. Enough. Even torturing you is boring.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Just get out.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Oh, Lancel, tell my friend Bronn

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: to please kill you if anything should happen to me.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Please kill me if anything should happen to Lord Tyrion.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It will be my pleasure.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Your Grace.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: What is it?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I'm sorry about your brother, Your Grace.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I wanted to let you know that people grieve for him.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Fools love a fool.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I grieve for him as well, for the boy he was, not the man he grew to be.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I need to speak to you

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: about what I saw in that cave. - I thought I made it clear to you

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: there'd be no need to speak to me on this matter.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Your Grace, I...

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I've never known you to need to hear a thing twice.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And I've never known you to hide from the truth.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You've come to lecture me on truth?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I've come to tell you that what I saw...

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: All my brother's bannermen have come to my side.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Except the Tyrells, who fled like cowards.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: They won't be able to resist us now.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Soon I shall be sitting on the Iron Throne.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Nothing is worth what this will cost you, not even the Iron...

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I'll hear no more about it.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Take a company of men, secure the perimeter.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: When do we sail for King's Landing?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: As soon as I've consolidated my troops.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We'll make short work of the Lannisters' fleet.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Once Blackwater Bay is cleared,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: we'll deliver our troops to their doorstep and take the city.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: That's not your concern.

cap: If you take King's Landing with her by your side, the victory will be hers.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I never thought I'd have reason to doubt your loyalty. Was I wrong?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Loyal service means telling hard truths.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Oh, truth again.

cap: All right, what's the truth?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The hard truth?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: She's a foreigner preaching her foreign religion.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Some believe she whispers orders in your ear and you obey.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: What do you believe?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: You won those bannermen from Renly.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Don't lose them to her.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We set out for King's Landing without Lady Melisandre.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: And you lead the fleet into Blackwater Bay.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Your Grace, I'm honoured, but my time on the sea

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: was spent evading ships, not attacking them.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The other lords won't be happy.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Most of those lords should consider themselves lucky

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I don't hang them for treason.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Hard truths cut both ways, Ser Davos.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: I've got it! I've got it!

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: So it's that one there at the top, on the right.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Buy my fruit, my lord. Fresh fruit.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Stannis has more infantry, more ships, more horses.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: What do we have?

cap: There's that mind of yours you keep going on about.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: What about your father?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: He hasn't sent a raven in weeks.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: He's very busy.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

cap: We won't be able to hold the city against Stannis,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: We are swollen, bloated, foul.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The king is a lost cause.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: It's the rest of us I'm worried about now.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

cap: Demon monkey.

cap: Stop.

cap: Stop!

cap: The Stony Shore's not far from Torrhen's Square.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The seat of the House of Tallhart,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: a more impressive prize than a few fishermen's daughters.

cap: What, you don't think we could take it? - No, we could.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

cap: And then...

cap: Take me to my ship.

cap: The Starks have overextended their lines.

cap: Now that summer's over, they'll have a hard time

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: keeping their men and horses fed.

cap: The Starks understand winter better than we ever will.

cap: The cold won't beat them.

cap: Our spies report growing discontent among the Northern lords.

cap: And I'm sure if those same spies snuck into our own encampments,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

cap: This is war, no one's content.

cap: We've underestimated the Stark boy for too long.

cap: You've been waiting for him to fail.

cap: We've worked through the night, my lord.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Girl.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Where are you from?

cap: I did.

cap: A man pays his debts.

cap: You saved me and the two I was with.

cap: We have to give them back.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: That is enough.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

cap: He was north of the Skirling Pass when the snows came.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Had to wait for the thaw.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: So it is possible for someone to survive out here on their own.

cap: Well, possible for the Halfhand.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Beautiful, isn't it?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Gilly would love it here.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: There's nothing more sickening than a man in love.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: About time you did something.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: At least you'll keep warm.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: The Fist of the First Men.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Think of how old this place is.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Before the Targaryens defeated the Andals,

cap: Before I die, please, stop talking.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Stupid.

cap: Smart people don't find themselves in places like this.

cap: I think they were afraid.

cap: I think they came here to get away from something.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Wildlings?

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: So you got to stand there waiting,

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: wondering.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: Aye, we'll live another day.

cap: Hurrah.

cap: Oh, I have not conducted this experiment.

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
cap: If I could tell you how many crazy old men I've seen pushing carts around army camps

name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
